peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the difference between a tiller and a cultivator?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Cultivators are smaller and easier to maneuver than tillers. It works well for day-to-day gardening tasks. What is a tiller? Tillers are more powerful than cultivators and have larger, heavy-duty tines that work the soil.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What was the cultivator used for?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The main function of the field cultivator is to prepare a proper seedbed for the crop to be planted into, to bury crop residue in the soil (helping to warm the soil before planting), to control weeds, and to mix and incorporate the soil to ensure the growing crop has enough water and nutrients to grow well during the ...
peopleAlsoAsk.title: Cultivator - Wikipedia

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the best use for a cultivator?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: A cultivator's objective is to break up clumps, get rid of (or bury) weeds and stones, and aerate seed beds in preparation for planting. Shallow cultivation uproots weeds and loosens soil around plants, making it easier for the air and water to penetrate deep into the soil.
